Our Team
David Wisner
General Manager
Brooksville Country Club
David has focused his life on education, sports and customer service. As a majority owner of the Brooksville Country Club, his goal is to provide members with a family friendly club for sports and entertainment. To achieve his dream, the ownership‚Äôs plans are to establish a top level sports academy along side the club, which will improve and enhance the sports offerings for members. The club will operate independently of the school but with deep integration of resources.
kelly lagedrost
Director of Golf
Brooksville Country Club
She began her golf career at the age of 8 at BCC. She attained the title of Florida High School State Champion while attending Hernando High School and was named Female Student Athlete of the Year while at USF.
Kelly served one year as USF‚Äôs Women‚Äôs Head Golf Coach. She was a member of the LPGA/Futures Tour for 10 years. Kelly is a current LPGA Class A Teaching Professional.
Allen Wilson
Golf Course Superintendent
Brooksville Country Club
Allen Wilson is a seasoned Golf Course Maintenance Professional and has experience maintaining many of Tampa Bay‚Äôs most renowned golf courses. Allen has a deep passion for golf course maintenance, and he takes pride in maintaining top quality conditions. He looks forward to bringing his experience to Brooksville Country Club.
Annery Garcia
Head Chef
Majestic Oaks at Brooksville Country Club Bar & Restaurant
Annery‚Äôs passion for cooking started early, experimenting with ingredients and creating delicious meals. She began her career as a personal chef for prominent New York families, then moved to Florida, working in restaurants and running a catering business. Now, she‚Äôs excited to lead
Majestic Oaks Restaurant as head chef
, bringing fresh ingredients and an American menu with Italian and international flavors. Stay tuned for upcoming events and specials!
Adam Godwin
CFO & Business Director
Brooksville Country Club / American Collegiate Academy
Adam has worked in education and executive management for almost 20 years, and currently serves as the CEO of Aston Educational Group, a sister company of Brooksville Country Club, that owns and operates over 80 schools in China, Vietnam and the US. After 15 years living and working in China, he is now based in Florida and helps guide the development of Brooksville Country Club, American Collegiate Academy, and the future development plans for both businesses. He brings finance, operations, marketing and planning expertise to the team. And unfortunately for him, spending more time at the golf course hasn‚Äôt seemed to help his golf game at all.
Nancy Shen
Executive Administrator
Brooksville Country Club
Nancy Shen is the Executive Administrator at the Brooksville Country Club and oversees membership accounts and services, bookkeeping and pickleball training. Nancy has a deep background in management having overseen administration of a prior business with over 150 locations. Nancy has traveled extensively internationally. Nancy also has a PPR pickleball coaching license, and helps bring in the top level players in the world to help train our members.

Tale of two courses front nine standard golf course back nine in and around and over old rock quarry. Tougher and more scenic. Staff is attentive very nice and interesting
Joe Large
Feedback from Google
I love this country course. Big old oaks, open fairways and old Cory holes on the back nine.
Vicki Anderson
Feedback from Google
Fun course. The back 9 tee shots are definitely not the typical view from a tee box on a Florida golf course. Greens were super slow but they were in good condition. Definitely recommend
Alan Matthew
Feedback from Google
The course was in great shape, greens were fast and rolled true.  Stay  in the fairways and in the right position and you will good, get out of position and you will be hard-pressed to make par.  Lunch was good with the restaurant and staff was very accommodating.  I would recommend the course to anyone that ask.
Dennie LaPorte
Feedback from Google
Playing at Brookville Country Club was an absolute delight! The meticulously maintained fairways and greens provided a top-notch golfing experience. The breathtaking views added an extra layer of enjoyment to every swing. The staff's hospitality and attention to detail truly made our visit unforgettable. Can't wait to tee off again at this hidden gem! ‚õ≥üåü #GolfingParadise #BrookvilleCountryClub
Jerry S.

(Required)
RECEIPT OF MEMBERSHIP:
I/WE (‚ÄúMember‚Äù) have applied for membership indicating the specific membership program noted at Brooksville Country Club. I hereby acknowledge receipt of the Membership Plan according to the rules and regulations administered and promulgated from time to time by the Brooksville Country Club. I am subject to such rules, terms and conditions set forth as stated. Violation or failure to abide by membership conditions may result in termination or suspension of membership.
MEMBERSHIP:
Brooksville Country Club remains sole owners and operators of the Club facilities, including all amenities provided. I hereby acknowledge that my membership does not award me any investment, equity or ownership interest in the Club facilities, nor does it deem me a vested party with easement to use the Club facilities. Members reserve no right where assets or negotiations are concerned. The Club reserves the exclusive right and discretion to modify the Membership Plan or make any other alterations in the terms and conditions of the membership or the Club facilities and to restrict or reserve usage of the Club facilities for maintenance, golf or tennis tournaments, promotional, charitable or other special events periodically. All memberships are subject to suspension and revocation with or without cause. In the event of any grievance or suit, between the Club and any member for any claim or matter, the prevailing party shall be liable to the other party for all costs and expenses including attorney‚Äôs fees (including appellate proceeding costs). Resignation from the club must be submitted in writing and provided 30 days advance notice. All resignations will become effective on the 1st day of the month following the 30 days advance notice.
PAYMENT AGREEMENT:
I hereby understand and agree that this contract is legally binding upon signing. I have read the contract and payment terms of obligation based on the chosen membership. If monthly installments are selected, member is required to pay the first and last month‚Äôs dues upon signing this Agreement and commits to the payment of additional monthly installments unless annual, semi-annual or other prepayment arrangements were received, accounted for and cleared. I further agree to be jointly and severally responsible for all charges and expenses incurred by other authorized family members and guests. I acknowledge that all dues and charges are payable automatically by credit/debit card on the 7th of each month. If the amount due is not received, the account will be considered delinquent, and club privileges will be suspended. The member will subsequently remain liable for the balance due, and all said discretionary fees and charges of the collections process will become the responsibility of stated member. In the event of failure to pay any amounts due to the Club, the Membership Fee or any portion thereof paid previously for the membership will be liquidated and all entitlement will be subject to the Club‚Äôs discretion.
HOLD HARMLESS:
I acknowledge the possibility of injury and risks associated with usage of the Club facilities. Every member shall be liable for any property damage and/or personal injury at the Club facilities, or any event or function that is coordinated, operated arranged or sponsored by the Club, caused by the member, any family member or guest. The cost of any such damage will be charged to the member‚Äôs account.
WAIVER AND RELEASE OF LIABILITY:
The Club urges and recommends you and all members to obtain a physical examination from a licensed physician before using any equipment or participating in any exercise program. All exercises or activities performed with or without the use of equipment or apparatus designed for exercise is at the member‚Äôs sole risk. The member assumes entire responsibility when using or selecting exercise programs, including selection of methods and types of equipment used. The Club shall not be liable to member for any negligence, claims, demands, injuries, damages, or actions causing injury to member‚Äôs person or property arising out of or in connection with the use by member of the services, facilities, and premises of the Club. The member is advised that personnel have no expertise in diagnosing, examining or treating medical conditions of any kind or effect of any specific exercise on said medical condition. Member fully understands and agrees that in consideration of participating in one or more of the fitness programs or using the facility, there is the possibility of accidental or other physical injury. Member agrees to assume the risk of injury and further, member hereby holds the club, its officers, owners, agents and employees harmless from all claims which may be brought against them by member or on member‚Äôs behalf for any such injuries or claims.
NO BAILOR/BAILEE RELATIONSHIP:
The parties hereto agree that this agreement shall not create a bailor/bailee relationship as to any personal property left or held by or at the club, including, but not limited to, clothing, workout equipment, automobiles, and car keys. Members are solely responsible for the security of their property brought onto or into the club premises and/or parking lot.
This agreement is performable in Hernando County, Florida. Within this agreement the singular shall include the plural, and the masculine the feminine. Member understands that this agreement shall be binding until resignation according to the rules and regulations of BGCC or until membership is terminated by BGCC pursuant to the rules and regulations of the Club.

THIS AGREEMENT
is entered into by and between Brooksville Country Club, LLC and Majestic Oaks at Brooksville Country Club, LLC, herein called the Club, and the undersigned duly registered Club member.
WHEREAS,
the Club owns and operates a swimming pool, fitness center, and pickleball/tennis courts for the convenience and use of its members and their guests, and
WHEREAS,
the Club is legally bound to comply with all statutory laws and regulations with respect to maintenance and operation of the swimming pool, fitness center, and tennis/pickleball courts, and
WHEREAS,
the Club has purchased insurance coverage to protect it from liability for accidents or injuries relating to or arising out of the use of these facilities. The pool and other facilities are periodically inspected by safety engineers to establish required safety precautions. The Club becomes liable if such standards and procedures are not applied or enforced, and
WHEREAS,
each Club member and their guests using the swimming pool, fitness center or tennis/pickleball courts must be familiar with the rules and procedures prescribed by the Club. Copies are available at the Club office and
WHEREAS,
the swimming pool is not equipped for night-time swimming. No swimmers are allowed to use the pool after dark, and
WHEREAS,
adult supervision is required for children under age 16 to use the Swimming Pool, Fitness Center or Tennis/Pickleball Courts, and
WHEREAS,
the pool gate must be locked at all times except during posted hours, and
WHEREAS,
upon signing this Agreement the undersigned member with the distinct understanding that use of the pool, fitness center, and tennis/pickleball courts is ‚ÄúAT THEIR OWN RISK‚Äù.
WHEREAS,
the undersigned member agrees that he/she will hold harmless and indemnify the Club for any injury or accident to members or their guests using the pool, fitness center or tennis/pickleball courts, and for any out-of-pocket expenses incurred by reason thereof, including any expenses or attorney fees that the Club may incur in defending any claim, judgment or other action as a result of such injury or out-of-pocket expenses of the member.

about us
Brooksville Country Club
Welcome to Brooksville Country Club
Where Nature's Beauty Meets
Golfing Excellence
our story
Nestled in the heart of Central Florida, Brooksville Country Club offers a golfing and leisure experience that stands out in its uniqueness and charm. Our club is set against a stunning backdrop of rolling landscapes, punctuated with majestic live oaks and the historical intrigue of an abandoned limestone mine. This setting not only captivates the eye but also provides a golfing journey unlike any other in the region.
A Course Like 
No Other
The course, starting gently, gradually unfolds into a more challenging experience as you approach the back nine, masterfully
designed by Bobby Weed
. It‚Äôs a layout that calls for strategic thinking and precision, offering a rewarding experience for both the casual and serious golfer.
Starting from the time you pull in the parking lot until the time you leave, you will receive friendly and professional customer service. A member of our courteous staff will be awaiting your arrival and check you in for your tee time.
Quality Conditions
Our commitment to excellence extends to the excellent condition of our fairways and greens. Meticulously maintained, they ensure a premium golfing experience every time you step onto the course.
beyond golf
Brooksville Country Club is more than just a golf course. We offer a range of amenities that cater to all aspects of leisure and fitness:
Majestic Oaks Restaurant
Under the culinary direction of Chef Mik, enjoy a dining experience that tantalizes your taste buds.
Learn More
Pickleball and Tennis
Challenge yourself on our new professional courts.
Learn More
Junior Golf Program
Led by Tom Shea, our program nurtures the budding talents of young golfers.
Learn More
Fitness Facility
Keep fit and active in our 
fully-equipped gym.
Learn More
Diverse Club Memberships
Choose a membership that best suits your lifestyle and enjoy exclusive privileges.
Learn More
A Melting Pot of
Talent
We pride ourselves on attracting and employing talents from across the globe. Among our esteemed team is Kelly Lagedrost, a celebrated inductee in the USF Athletics Hall of Fame, who brings her expertise and passion to our club.
